According to 2018 estimates, Bradenville has 396 residents. The estimated median household income is $38,551, compared to the national average of $61,937.

The estimated poverty rate is 26.3%, compared to the national average of 13.1%. 100% of Bradenville residents are white, and 85.6% are high school graduates or higher.<ref>{{cite web |title=2018 American Community Survey, 5-Year Estimates |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/profile?q=Bradenville%20CDP,%20Pennsylvania&g=1600000US4208024 |publisher=United States Census Bureau |access-date=March 7, 2020}}</ref>

